st interest in the limelight after the high-pressure years of building Uber. He might now prefer to focus on quieter, less public-facing ventures.\n\n*   **Philanthropic Focus:** Camp seems to focus his public activity through his philanthropic efforts. It's possible he focuses his charitable contributions and public communication through his foundation.\n\nIn summary, it's likely a combination of personal preference, strategic communication choices, and perhaps a desire to avoid controversy that contributes to the lack of interviews with Garrett Camp.\n",
